column5: Hi all, Going down this weekend to fish Lake Manitouwabing.  Don't really know this lake.  Can anyone give me some insight.  We are staying on Tait Island.  Hope all have a great long weekend.  The weather should be great.  ps.  pike, walleye, bass, lakers .  fishing in that order  Take care  Adrian
Would this be Lake Manitouwaning on Manitoulin Island?
No, McKellar Township HWY 124 East of Parry Sound

I fished the lake as a kid once a summer and it's how I got hook on the north. I can't remember names and places on the lake as they didn't seem to matter back then. I do remember catching lots of pike, bass and some walleye. I do also remember seeing some monsters coming out of the lake in the high 40's.  Hope you had a great time up there.
